main event: A round, red object was sighted going straight up and headed east before fading away.
interesting points: The object was observed for 3 minutes.
The sighting occurred at 0330Z on August 13, 1955.
The witness was a 46-year-old plumber located in Alhambra, California.
The weather was dark and clear with light winds from the west, and there was no other traffic in the area.
